comment: $11 at Walmart. Woody with some rye[?] spice and a little sweetness. That's it.  Nothing more to see here.  Nothing complex by any stretch of the imagination, but sippable nonetheless.
Had a cool bottle. First bottle was a bourbon so I bought a cheap whiskey. I’ll try a rye next

Color is a golden amber with a vanilla, candy corn, and grass smell. It has warming taste that is tart and dill. The whiskey is distilled at Florida Caribbean Distillery in Lake Alfred, Florida. Great used in cocktails or just drinking neat.
